# THIS FILE MUST LIVE AT THE GIT ROOT (`probo/`), because that is where Vercel is
# linked (see ./.vercel) and therefore what it uploads from. A .vercelignore
# inside `proofbook/` or `proofbook/web/` is silently ignored — which is how an
# upload of 18,422 files (the root node_modules + .next) blew the 15,000 limit,
# and how the uploader ended up trying to read a UNIX SOCKET at
# proofbook/.anchor/test-ledger/admin.rpc (`Unknown system error -102`).
#
# Paths are relative to THIS directory.

# dependency trees — Vercel installs its own
proofbook/node_modules
proofbook/web/node_modules
**/node_modules

# build output
proofbook/web/.next
proofbook/target
proofbook/.anchor
proofbook/test-ledger
proofbook/.surfpool
**/*.so

# server-side services — the web app only reaches ../../shared
proofbook/keeper
proofbook/api
proofbook/db
proofbook/programs
proofbook/migrations
proofbook/scripts
proofbook/tests
proofbook/docs
proofbook/backups

# secrets
**/.env
**/.env.*
